Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.53,0:00:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I first became aware of myself in a coin locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that eerie darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.06,0:00:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.69,0:00:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blue sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.65,0:00:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blue ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.78,0:00:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.66,0:00:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blue window frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.41,0:00:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.21,0:00:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gunther Milch, arrested in 1988 for robbing an\Narmored car from the Bavarian BASF Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.60,0:00:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did time in Badenburg Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.35,0:00:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Escaped in '91.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.39,0:00:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spent half a year cutting through the iron bars...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.19,0:00:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a nail sharpened into a file.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.11,0:00:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was caught three days later...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.11,0:00:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was sent to Kreiner Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.44,0:01:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in 1993...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.36,0:01:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,escaped through a drainage pipe in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.57,0:01:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prison uniform, soaked with excrement, was\Nfound three days later on a nearby riverbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.49,0:01:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrested for attempted robbery of a Maximilian\N& Co. paycheck delivery truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.25,0:01:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In '97, escaped from a shower stall in Ingeburg Prison...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.88,0:01:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after spending a year, and a half\Ndigging a hole with a spoon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.09,0:01:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.72,0:01:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The toilet here stinks pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.18,0:01:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I escaped through a sewer once, so I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.68,0:01:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.32,0:01:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a gloomy look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.24,0:01:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Face forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.49,0:01:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm not mistaken, that's Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.03,0:01:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.24,0:01:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think he'd look so depressed and hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.87,0:03:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.93,0:03:27.14,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(321,200)\pos(364,353)}Lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.87,0:03:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In '86, the poisonings at Eisler Memorial\Nof Director Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surgical Director Oppenheim, and Dr. Boyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still deny any involvement?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.14,0:03:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we started the interrogation,\Nyou haven't said a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma, what are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.65,0:03:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you keep silent, you'll still be\Nprosecuted and made to stand trial...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.32,0:03:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you won't stand a chance in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:03:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.74,0:04:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us everything and remove the\Nburden from your shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.33,0:04:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.37,0:04:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milch has stomach problems!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.55,0:04:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}rer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.67,0:04:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Dr. D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}rer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.38,0:04:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor's currently in the interrogation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.72,0:04:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter drank some sort of cleaning fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.43,0:04:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he choking on his own vomit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.35,0:04:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.44,0:04:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't breathe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.98,0:04:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.40,0:04:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we'll have to use him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.70,0:04:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.37,0:04:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have a look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.71,0:04:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.39,0:05:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring some hot water...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.80,0:05:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a towel, and a change of clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.76,0:05:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.35,0:05:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be contagious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you pretending to be sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.62,0:05:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show some mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.50,0:05:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the first doctor to see through my act so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.04,0:05:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh, I figured that if I got sent to the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.84,0:05:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd have a better chance of escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how I rob armored cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I jump out in front of the truck and pretend to be sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the guards run out of the truck to help me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.02,0:05:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my accomplices show up with guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never killed anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.36,0:05:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna escape with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a gloomy-looking face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.87,0:06:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Staying in a place like this will suck the life out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.08,0:06:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate cramped places the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.84,0:06:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I first became aware of myself in a coin locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.22,0:06:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that eerie darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.80,0:06:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my parents went to work, they put me\Nin there and I'd eagerly await their return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.77,0:06:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's go to Tunisia someday."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My parents used to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.57,0:06:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If work goes well today, let's go to Tunisia."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.20,0:06:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I waited for three days, and\Nthey never came back for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.54,0:07:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My parents must have left me behind\Nand went to Tunisia on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.26,0:07:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get out of this cramped place...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.60,0:07:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.39,0:07:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a gloomy-looking face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no hope in your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not like mine, where hope exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.49,0:07:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do if they catch you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.99,0:07:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just escape again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times it takes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.87,0:07:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.58,0:07:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to say nothing again today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.05,0:07:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.84,0:07:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even as we speak, something terrible is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.84,0:07:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to hear the truth quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.51,0:07:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you won't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't believe a word I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.68,0:07:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.53,0:08:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.53,0:08:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.95,0:08:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sentence the accused to twenty years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my dad was found guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.41,0:08:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my path in life was decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.54,0:08:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the war...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my dad moved from Sudeten,\NCzechoslovakia, to Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where he opened a small radio station in 1949.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, during the cold war between\NEast and West Germany in the 60s...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.51,0:08:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was arrested for being a spy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.47,0:08:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and for the murder of a Bundestag member's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.98,0:08:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His arrest was a huge shock to West German society.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.73,0:08:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad pleaded innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.73,0:08:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but was still sentenced to twenty years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.48,0:08:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom continued to proclaim my dad's innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until she died in '71.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.53,0:08:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad died in prison in '72, filled with resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.08,0:09:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In '73, while I was in high school...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.25,0:09:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nmy dad's innocence was proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After I graduated from D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorf University...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.71,0:09:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a job at the Hoffmann law firm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a major firm at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won my first case...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.01,0:09:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,proving the charges were false\Nand the defendant was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.56,0:09:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I consistently won a not-guilty\Nverdict in every case I argued.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.48,0:09:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Fritz Verdeman...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,went from being the son of a spy, to\Na "star" in the legal world, overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.03,0:09:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.99,0:09:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The radio station my dad managed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.70,0:09:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,started and ended each day with this song.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.21,0:09:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To people like you who lived in the East...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this song may seem like a symbol of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.72,0:09:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.43,0:09:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad died in prison while asserting his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:09:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to let him rest in peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.89,0:10:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to take on every case in which...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.85,0:10:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a possibility that the defendant\Nmay actually be innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.94,0:10:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.48,0:10:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about Dr. Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elsa, how'd your checkup at the maternity center go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.03,0:10:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.83,0:10:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said I could expect the baby any day now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.91,0:10:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just passed a man in the lobby, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.67,0:10:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.84,0:10:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he the one you mentioned before?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.34,0:10:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.21,0:10:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alfred Baul...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me to represent Dr. Tenma with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.43,0:10:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you turn down Dr. Tenma's case the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, because the client at the time\Nwas Hans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.77,0:10:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know why a billionaire would\Nwant me to defend Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.32,0:10:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this time, the reason is clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.82,0:11:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What reason would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.82,0:11:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The clients who brought the case to Baul were...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.33,0:11:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the patients whose lives were saved by Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.21,0:11:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This much is certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.63,0:11:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma was an outstanding doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you take the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I won the case, the billionaire\Nwould pay me handsomely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.35,0:11:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But not so with the patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.31,0:11:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were working solely for profit...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.15,0:11:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd have a bigger office by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.20,0:11:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.20,0:11:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is "Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.84,0:11:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.00,0:11:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.55,0:12:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That aside, let's go get something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the new life that's about to be born...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.23,0:12:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you have to eat enough for two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.56,0:12:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.15,0:12:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The baby's kicking because it's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, honey, which restaurant would you like to go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.74,0:12:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about that one place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.83,0:12:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.62,0:12:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,disappeared in the midst of the blaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.16,0:12:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.96,0:12:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I start from the beginning again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.43,0:12:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll repeat it as many times as I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As many times... as the truth takes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.10,0:12:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the fourth one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.68,0:12:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lawyers who wanted to represent\Nme in court all suggested...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.02,0:12:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I plead guilty to some of the charges...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.98,0:12:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lighten my sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all they could talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.11,0:13:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to me that you don't really care\Nabout proving your innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rather, you want to prove the existence\Nof a certain young man named Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.29,0:13:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.08,0:13:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, you don't need a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.76,0:13:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.76,0:13:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did all of this {\i1}really{\i0} begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.84,0:13:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, when a boy who was shot\Nin the head was brought in...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.35,0:13:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, did anything happen before that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.27,0:13:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Turkish woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.23,0:13:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Give my husband back!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.15,0:13:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}People's lives aren't equal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's lives are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.42,0:13:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I made the right decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.42,0:14:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell if a patient is good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.30,0:14:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My crime was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.42,0:14:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My crime was saving that boy's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.06,0:14:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does a doctor have the right to choose to save a life...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.35,0:14:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,based on whether the patient is good or evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.15,0:14:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}lives aren't equal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.61,0:14:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I can't decide...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.07,0:14:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same way with lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.12,0:14:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know if the people we defend are good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is the list of people who asked me to represent you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.21,0:14:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Michal Hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.97,0:14:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stefan Kramp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.93,0:14:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Franz Kiefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Rudolf Huber.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.39,0:14:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kiefer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.72,0:14:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Huber...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.14,0:14:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.52,0:14:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Horst Henschel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.44,0:14:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Riidiger Hoss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.85,0:15:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hoss, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.44,0:15:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right... I wonder if he's living\Nhappily with his grandkids?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.11,0:15:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.15,0:15:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.74,0:15:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.37,0:15:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.41,0:15:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will represent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawyers can't tell if a person is good or evil, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.84,0:15:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we represent someone, there's\Nonly one thin we can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.88,0:15:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.31,0:15:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One more glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.23,0:15:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said one more!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.35,0:15:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.15,0:15:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since when did this bar start refusing to serve customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.28,0:15:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.37,0:15:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just laughed at me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.37,0:16:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.37,0:16:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You looked at me and laughed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.00,0:16:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.46,0:16:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.42,0:16:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,used to come to my house to kiss ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.30,0:16:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the assistant manager at Nordrhein-West Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.18,0:16:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After going to the trouble of coming back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.89,0:16:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva Heinemann has returned to D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorf!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.03,0:16:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for filling me in on these important details...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I heard you were going\Nto be Dr. Tenma's lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I started trying to get in touch with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.41,0:16:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for being difficult to reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been all over the place asking about the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.04,0:16:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.13,0:16:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, asking Dr. Tenma's supporters, his former patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.59,0:16:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did they say anything...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.68,0:16:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma seems to be an outstanding doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.89,0:16:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you get any important evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.10,0:17:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.52,0:17:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hoping to find a witness to confirm Dr. Tenma's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.40,0:17:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, if we want to prove Tenma's innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.07,0:17:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we need to be able to prove that\Nthis Johan person actually exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Dr. Tenma attempting to\Nshoot this young man, Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.58,0:17:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to withhold that part of your testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.91,0:17:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... that's the only event that proves Johan exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.75,0:17:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether or not Johan exists, Tenma is still innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.30,0:17:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hear me out, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.09,0:17:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All this country wants is a scapegoat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My child will be born soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.98,0:17:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For my unborn child's sake, I want true justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The judges and prosecutors who want an easy solution...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have groundlessly sentenced innocent people\Nfor crimes they never committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:17:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our unjust country must repent for its sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what's important, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.75,0:18:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.71,0:18:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for a particular person right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.75,0:18:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.21,0:18:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She may know something vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.97,0:18:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.38,0:18:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma's former fiancee...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.80,0:18:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.47,0:18:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong, Dr. Reichwein?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.77,0:18:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She came with me to this city...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.98,0:18:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all laughing... Everyone is laughing at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.53,0:18:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They take one look at me and laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.08,0:18:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva, about what I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.79,0:18:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:18:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please meet with the lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.09,0:18:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Tenma's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.09,0:18:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you before, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.13,0:18:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.43,0:19:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,actually tried to shoot him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.18,0:19:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was surprised when you first told me about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.19,0:19:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you didn't shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, I didn't shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.40,0:19:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.78,0:19:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it would've been a problem if he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let the man who ruined my life die that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.49,0:19:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want him to rot in prison for the rest of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.00,0:19:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,forever regretting that he dumped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.56,0:19:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.04,0:20:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened? Did you have a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.67,0:20:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard... three gunshots...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.43,0:20:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.64,0:20:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blonde boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.02,0:20:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.40,0:20:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.48,0:20:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you seen Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.69,0:20:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.86,0:20:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A symbol of freedom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.74,0:20:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Verdeman, your wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.71,0:20:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's gone into labor, and she was\Ntaken to the maternity center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.58,0:20:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Klinger, call Mr. Baul immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.88,0:20:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please ask him to meet with Dr. Tenma in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.84,0:21:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your lawyer, Baul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.35,0:21:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was asked to meet with you today...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.89,0:21:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you doing? Getting enough sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.19,0:21:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.81,0:21:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.86,0:21:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was originally right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get used to holding a pen with my left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.62,0:21:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My right hand won't move anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.62,0:21:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.54,0:21:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have lost quite a bit of weight...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.13,0:21:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, I impressed even myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.13,0:21:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I escaped that sea of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.85,0:21:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You actually shot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.99,0:22:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.20,0:22:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,may not be used to holding a pen\Nbut it can handle a gun just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.45,0:22:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.91,0:22:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking of killing someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.33,0:22:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your former fiancee...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.09,0:22:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.84,0:22:31.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:47.40,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:25.94,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.94,0:23:34.36,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:36.82,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.93,0:23:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
